    "blurb": "Six hundred and ninety-three kilometres above the Earth, a European radar satellite passes over Ukraine every twelve days. It does not see in colour; it does not need daylight or clear skies. It sends out pulses of microwaves and listens for what comes back. Over the four years since Russia's full-scale invasion, those returning signals have built up a quiet, parallel record of a war that has been fought in part against an electricity grid, strike by strike, plant by plant.",
